          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>93 and 95 Sixth
                                        Avenue</placeName>.</p>
                              <p/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">The Metropolitan Academy and</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">Gymnasium are now ready for the</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">reception of pupils.</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">The Faculty will be pleased to</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">have you visit the Institution at</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">your convenience.</p>
                              <p/>
                              <p rend="align(center)"><date>Nov. 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>,
                                                  1852</date>.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>8 Dec '52</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Dr Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Rev &amp; Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">As your friend, the<lb/>
                                        <persName>Rev Simon C. Noot<add>?</add></persName>, is the
                                        Prof of<lb/> Hebrew, in the “Metropolitan Academy,”<lb/> And
                                        as I am not so competent<lb/> to judge of his
                                        qualifications, as<lb/> yourself, yet I so admire him<lb/>
                                        as a gentleman and a teacher<lb/> that I very much desire to
                                        have<lb/> his situation permanent and<lb/> profitable,—I
                                        have taken the<lb/> liberty to send you two paragraphs<lb/>
                                        one from the New York Daily Times<lb/> The other in the
                                        Phrenological<lb/> Journal, to aid you some-<lb/> (over)</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>what in forming an idea of<lb/> our Institution.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Be pleased to say for us<lb/> what you think
                                        proper, in<lb/> order to place the advantages<lb/> of our
                                        Institution before the<lb/> Hebrew Citizens of
                                                  <placeName>New York</placeName>,<lb/> and send
                                        your bill to your</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Most Obdt</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">Servt</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">Stephen J. Sedgwick</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>93 &amp; 95, 6, Avenue</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Near Washington Square</placeName>
                              </p>
